cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with image classification and uses human gaze as auxiliary information. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves human-computer interaction, which suggests the category cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as the second most likely. The paper proposes a method that involves learning a compatibility function, which falls under the category of machine learning, cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves data collection and analysis, which suggests the category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval, as it deals with finding relevant information from auxiliary data, which suggests the category cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
